title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson Model 38 J Frame Airweight Pre-Lock Collector Quality
postcontent: I am selling my Smith & Wesson Model 38 revolver. This is a compact .38 special 5 shot revolver with an Airweight frame and shrouded hammer, but the hammer spur can be cocked back so it can be fired either single action or double action. I bought this gun myself new in August, 1984 and it was carried in a padded nylon holster in a purse maybe 6 times, then stored in a dry environment. The finish is 100% original. There is an almost imperceptible turn mark on the cylinder and of course there is the wear mark on the breech face behind the cylinder from the spring-loaded pin in center of the ejector, which is visible with the cylinder opened. Other than that, the gun is flawless--it looks like it did when it came out if the box. There are no defects. The finish is as new. The grips are original and as new. I have the original box and all original paperwork. Everything. I have a 30 year old box of bullets that were bought with the gun and the box still has rounds in it, so it has less than 50 rounds through it in its lifetime. Anything that looks like a finish flaw in the pictures is just glare. This is really a time capsule gun and would be a prized addition to the collection of any lover of Smith & Wesson revolvers.  And there is no S&W lock on this gun!!! You are welcome to examine the gun in person in Columbus, Ohio. Shipping will be $35 and only to your FFL. Cash only in person and Postal Money Order, Moneygram or Western Union otherwise.  And "Postal" means a money order issued by the U.S. Postal Service.  Don't let this one get away--you will likely never find another one this nice.

title: For Sale:  7.62x54 Ammo - The Unusual/Hard to Find Stuff
postcontent:
Here's an assortment of 7.62 x 54 ammo that I dug out of my ammo locker recently that's hard to find anymore. 

(5) 20 round boxes of Hungarian Yellow/Silver Tip.This ammo was made in 1988 which is practically brand new in the world of 7.62x54  ammo. It features a heavy FMJ 182 grain bullet with a steel core.It's loaded in lacquered steel cases giving a pleasant shiny gray look.
The bullet and primer are both sealed with a red lacquer. I've shot a ton of this long ago when it was available and it's some of the very best ammo I've ever used. It's quite accurate, packs a heavy punch and it penetrates like crazy- far more than the light ball steel core ammo available today.The only flaw with this ammo is that recoil is noticeably heavier. Asking $75 for the 100 rounds. 

(5) 20 round boxes Russian made Match Ammo. This ammo was specifically loaded for accuracy. Tolerances are tighter and it uses a match grade propellant. It's brass case with a heavy FMJ 182 grain boat-tail bullet. It was made in 1971, but is bright, shiny and sure fire. It's without a doubt the most accurate ammo of this caliber that I've ever shot and I was able to routinely achieve sub-MOA 5 shot groups with a nice Finnish M27 rifle I used to own. It also performed very nicely in my Mosins and a SVT40. Asking $90 for the 100 rounds. 

(5) 20 round boxes East German M39 7.62x54 ammo. M39 ammo was originally designed as practice/training ammo primarily for machine guns. It's loaded with special black 124 grain FMJ steel core bullet. Velocity is not reduced, and the thought process was that the lighter projectile would travel less far than standard weight bullets. It's definitely not your typical training ammo as it penetrates 1/4" steel plate with ease at 100 yards. One big benefit is that felt recoil is greatly reduced because of the light weigh 124 grain bullet making it suitable for younger shooters and the ladies. This ammo is nearly impossible to find anymore and I've had it stashed away for many years. Asking $100 for the 100 rounds. 

 Pickup in the Brandon area. You must be at least 21 to purchase.

title: For Sale:  Russian 7.62x38R Nagant Ammo - 20 Boxes, 280 Rounds
postcontent:
I found a near full spam can of this Russian made 7.62x38 ammo recently while cleaning my ammo vault. I've owned at least a half dozen Nagant Revolvers over the years and fired them extensively. To me they were always one of the finest surplus handguns ever brought to the states. That said I've always found that the real Russian surplus ammo was the very best shooting ammo. It's clean, dependable and designed specifically for the Nagant. Plus it features a heavier 108 grain bullet with a steel core while the commercially loaded stuff has a lead core 98 grain bullet. Then to me at least the Russian ammo seemed to be loaded noticeably hotter than what you can get from PPU or Fiocchi. I suppose it's a liability issue? The last piece is that the Russian ammo always shot more accurately. The only negative at all is that this ammo does use a corrosive primer so cleaning your gun is a must after using. Listing is for (20) 14 boxes or 280 rounds total. Head stamp is 38-77 meaning it was produced at the Russian State Factory at Yuryusan, Russia in 1977. However it looks like it  
was made yesterday. 

Asking price is $150. FTT with pickup in the Brandon area. You must be at least 21 to

title: For Sale/Trade:  COLT Collectors!  "All American model 2000" Police 9mm -Very Limited Production - Mfg 1993
postcontent:
This is an awesome piece of history!   This would be a great piece for a collector and with so few of them made, they have tripled in value in recent years and they just continue to go up. I have handed this to friends/ dealers and so far most that have handled this pistol  do not know what it is and it certainly is a conversation piece!
 They made very few of these pistols as they had a poor reputation for a few reasons.  This particular pistol was just received back from Colt for maintenance, work and a recall to address many of those issues.  I have not fired it since I have received it back, however it was test fired at the factory.  *IF* you can find one without all the recall work done, you can find them cheaper.  This one was all serviced at Colt April 2014 and it should be better than new (and more valuable)!

CONDITION:  It is in absolutely top notch condition currently.  It comes with one 15 round magazine. 

HISTORY:
The Colt 2000 or All American 2000 is a polymer or aluminum-alloy framed, locked-breech, rotary bolt, semiautomatic 9mm handgun with a magazine capacity of 15 rounds. Designed by C. Reed Knight (Of Knights Armament) and Eugene Stoner,(Designer of the M16/AR-15) as Colt's entry into the marketplace of the high-capacity polymer framed handguns of the early 1990s; it was believed by Colt that this pistol would recapture their stake in the police market as Police Departments across the United States switched from double-action revolvers to semiautomatic pistols.  It was hoped that sales of this pistol might save the troubled company from bankruptcy on the heels of recovering from the UAW labor strike.

FUNCTIONALITY:  
The Colt 2000's internal workings were based on older firearms designs from the early twentieth century.  The rotating barrel, for example, was based on that of the Steyr 1912 and the roller-locking mechanism was based on a design used by the French Manufacture d'Armes et des Cycles de Saint-Etienne since 1914.  These features allow the barrel and slide to work as a unit moving to the rear until the barrel lug rotates into the cam-block and stops. The barrel lugs then align to allow the slide to continue its travel to the rear and extraction and ejection of the spent round occurs. The pistol breaks down into seven major parts for disassembly.

This is a very good pistol for what it is- a great collector for only $575!  The lowest price in the country on Armlist!

title: For Sale:  Mil-Spec Semi-Auto AR-15 - Comes w/ magazines, fore-grip, laser mount, carrying case and ammunition!
postcontent:
I have a NEW AR-15 (Semi-Automatic) for sale that was built by me from parts that were purchased from several different manufacturers. This rifle was constructed in 2014 with 100% mil-spec quality parts. Palmetto State Armory produced the lower receiver frame however I personally put the rifle's parts together. This is NOT a store bought rifle being re-sold after a few uses. This is a brand new rifle that was constructed by me and modified by me to meet certain standards of quality and to have certain features that are NOT featured on store bought rifles.

Keep in mind that Surplus Arms and Ammunition did barrel the upper receiver for me and install the muzzle break but other than that this rifle was built locally by me.

16" Barrel chambered for 5.56 NATO and .223 Remington loads.

Barrel is threaded and does have a standard A2 flash hider installed. Also, this is NOT a pencil barrel. It's a standard .750" barrel.

Chrome lined chamber and barrel prevents corrosion and promotes long barrel life.

1 in 7 twist rate keeps heavier bullets stable in flight.

Mid-Length hand guard and gas system (same plane).

Upper receiver is an A3 flat top which is optic ready.

Sling and sling attachment are already installed (not found on most off-the-shelf rifles)!

6 position stock with mil-spec spring and buffer tube.

Mil-spec, MPI tested, phosphate coated BCG.


This rifle has several features you will NOT find with an off-the-shelf AR-15:

Polished feed ramps prevent jamming and other malfunctions with match grade hollow point bullets. This rifle can be used in competition or for hunting where it's legal to do so.

The single stage trigger has had its pull weight reduced from 8 pounds to 6.5 pounds.

Flip up, removable iron sights have already been installed on this rifle and sighted in for 100 yards distance.

Picatinny/Weaver rails have already been installed onto the hand guard allowing the addition of a bi-pod, fore grip, laser/light mount, etc.

This rifle also comes with 5 magazines. You are not going to find retail stores offering 5 magazines with their rifles unless you purchase them separately. I buy my magazines in bulk and can pass on the savings to my customers. They are brand new and still in their original packaging.

The rifle also comes with a carrying case. Some companies offer carrying cases but very rarely. This rifle will come with a nice carrying case that has a shoulder strap, smooth nylon inner lining and the ability to have room for a scope on top of the rifle.
